text: The orginal trilogy was awful with exceptions from spiderman 2 but that movie.still had some really corny moments. The first spiderman was good and i.admit its a classic but it lacked backround info of how he got his powers and his parents. And i thought they did a terrible job on the green goblin. And i dnt understand at the end how he survived getting hit with a bomb????   Spiderman 2 was the best out of all.of them. But i didnt like how he lost his powers becuase it got to hard for him and became a weak corny nerd who wouldnt help somone getting robbed because hes.not spiderman anymore! And i thought is was stupid how he got his powers back becuase of mj. I mean rly what about the guy u just let get mugged?   Spiderman 3 was just terrible they tried to cram so much into it and it was just a mess. I liked how they tried to do venom but they shoulda just focused on him for the whole movie and.not make spiderman a emo guy wearing eye liner. I also didnt like how they got eric forman to play venom. I thought that fezz was just gonna pop outa no where along with the rest of the crew. And making sandman uncle bens real killer was just bad storytelling and a  way just to get another super villian. And there was just too much crying!  The amazing spiderman is the best spiderman movie out of all of them! They showed why peters parents left him with his ant and uncles. And showed how smart he rly was like in the comics such as making his web shooters. They also showed his sense of humor witch also goes back to  the comics witch in the sam ramis triogy really lacked of and when they did show it ir was really corny! They showed how his powers worked for him and had a pretty good backround on the lizard and what he was trying to do.  The amazing spiderman 2 was a good sequel but lacked alot.of backround info! It felt rushed and lacked alot lf backround info Such as harry coming out of no where and then all of a sudden turning into the green goblin in the last 15 min of the movie along with rhino witch they failed to do by making him a robot and having 2 min.of screen time! I also think that electo was good but his reasonings for turning bad was just poorly writtin and i felt like they were trying to hard to make max a nerd and a nobody! The fighting was amazing but i also think they killed gwen off to early and didnt rly explain wat had happend or what happend after she had died the next scene was her funeral.

author: Casey Mollenhauer

text: I watched this in the cinema with big expectations since I've watched the trailers a bunch of time. I've also watched the first one and I was severely disappointed with it. But I thought of giving this sequel a chance since the trailers looked awesome. This is the first time in my long years of watching movies that I feel like leaving the cinema while the film was playing. It bored me to death, the film is too cheesy, and it focused too much on Peter and Gwen's relationship. It may be a good flick for chicks, but not to those who seek to see a superhero in action. Rhino, Electro and other villains in the trailers are just a side story. Don't get me wrong, I love Spiderman, and I love all of it's comic book version. But this movie sucks, and if the writers and the director are trying to set apart themselves from Tobey's version, well, they have succeeded in doing just that.. Tobey's Spidey is far better than this Bollywood version of spiderman.¬† My advice, Do yourself a favor and buy Tobey's Spiderman Trilogy. It's way better than this, believe me. :)¬†

text: Harry in this trailer was way more interesting than the way he was shown in the movie. At least here, his presence and the fact that he's Peter's best friend don't feel shoehorned into the movie just so we can get to the Goblin part. He actually seems more charismatic, mysterious, magnetic and even more of a threat to Spider-Man here - the guy has Peter and Aunt May under surveillance! They had to be under surveillance for a reason but in the movie there's no surveillance and he doesn't even realise Spider-Man and Peter are the same person until he flies onto the scene and sees Gwen, finally putting 2 and 2 together.  This trailer version of Harry is what should have been in the final cut

I see a few comments saying Garfield is a bad Spiderman/Peter and I completely disagree. I think he is great and this movie being bad was not at all because of him or Emma Stone. Cool action, a bit depressing, definitely disappointing, yet still has lots of potential for the future.

text: My idea for the movie would have been that in the beginning, Norman Osborn hires Rhino as the Rhino to retrieve a few, for story purposes plutonium vials for him to create a super weapon that he intends to sell to a foreign buyer. Spider man, having known that Rhino has a mercenary like agenda, stops him and demands him to tell him who is his employer but Rhino refuses to tell and is sent to jail. Meanwhile the board of Oscorp become suspicious of what Norman Osborn is doing and plan to have him removed of the board of directors. Knowing that Spidey would become a threat to him as he recognises the spider DNA enhancements from the genetic spiders, Norman decides to inject himself with a serum and turns into the Goblin. Later Max Dillon falls into a tank of eels and turns into Electro where he heads to time square. During this time the board of directors remove Norman Osborne as CEO of Oscorp which forces Norman to return as the green goblin and kill the board of directors which is reported across New York but not before Spidey defeats Electro and imprisoned him in Ravenscroft.   With the buyer wanting the super weapon soon, Norman realises that he needs more money to continue so he robs a bank as the green goblin but flees after being defeated by Spidey. Knowing that Spidey is becoming a major problem and that after watching records of Electro in action Norman as the goblin frees him from Ravenscroft and forms an alliance-the same to rhino after freeing him from prison. Norman has finished building the weapon which is a biological bomb that can kill anyone within it's radius and after betraying his unknown buyer, the green goblin decides to use it on New York city while Rhino and Electro hold the entire city hostage to lure Spidey into a trap. Spidey falls for it and is overwhelmed by the three villains but Gwen arrives to help (like in the movie).   There she and Spidey work together to take down both Electro and Rhino in which electro is grounded and rhino dies. Gwen attempts to stop the bomb from being deployed but is captured by the goblin. The goblin finally lures Spidey to the clock tower and the two fight brutally while Gwen dangles below. Spidey  finally stops the bomb from going off while goblin throws a hail of pumpkin bombs at him.  Spidey slings them back with a web net killing Norman Osborn while Gwen falls down. Since I brutally hate Mary Jane Watson, Spidey saves Gwen from her death. Harry learning that Spidey killed his dad, breaks out Electro where he explains he wants four other guys to help them kill Spidey. The movie ends with Electro saying let's go catch a spider.  Notes:  The plot from the first movie never happened, it is completely different. This is just an idea. Harry was there during the final battle. And the only subplot is Gwen and Peter's relationship. Like I said this how I wanted the movie to go like. Oh yeah in the third one I came up with, Peter dies in Gwen's arms from Harry's sinister six with Aunt May finding out Peter's secret identity as well. this establishes Miles Morales becoming the next Spidey in which it ends with a spider from Harry's Oz formula biting Miles on the hand with him saying "Oh no"

text: Garfield was pretty good as Parker, he  really added a great dimension to the character. I like Peter portrayed as a normal  teen and not incredibly weak and nerdy. In the second movie the studio absolutely wasted Rhino character, he was miscast and written horribly. The same can be said of green goblins transformation and fight scene with Spiderman, entire thing felt rushed. I like the setup for sinister six too bad it was never realized. I think the character he developed would have been a great addition to marvel universe, I   don't understand why the moviemakers wouldn't want a strong version of Spider-Man to join the cast of characters. Instead we got a kid that needs a lot of maturing compared to already established cast of marvel world.

text: I really appreciate these Andrew Garfield spiderman movies because they were very serious and had incredible CGI. The director wasn't afraid to experiment with darker tones, character deaths, and intense action sequences. Homecoming was a joke compared to both these movies and I felt it didn't take itself seriously enough. The CGI was pretty bad and it wasn't entertaining. There weren't any memorable action sequences that I would want to rewatch. I feel like the MCU is too afraid to use darker tones and experiment with new ideas because they want to play it safe with the critics. Overall, I truly enjoyed the Andrew Garfield spiderman films and felt that they were much more serious and action-packed compared to most MCU films, which tend to be a joke.

text: The movie turns 6 today! still my #1 movie of 2014; it feels like they went back to the colorful fun tone of the Raimi trilogy, that 2012 movie was too much like Batman and almost made me officially give up wanting to see this character on the screen again thank god they got back on track this time around; the suit feels more like it was right out of the pages of the comic, the POV swinging shots are incredible, my dad loved being a part of the action which is amazing to look at, the chemistry between Garfield and Stone is the highlight of the movie and considering it's all leading to her death it makes it that much more impactful,  keep in mind there's a lot of themes and foreshadowing of time being precious and how little of it we have not to mention the sins of the fathers follow to our children think about how the fight on the plane with Richard Parker mirrors the fight in the clock tower between Peter and Harry Electro looks terrific trust me that yellow and green suit would've been laughable if they did that version yet his character seems very secondary I like Dane Dehaan as Harry you buy their friendship when you first see them together, pretty much everyone calls him a young Leonardo DiCaprio  still shocked they managed to cram so much material in 2 and a half hours although i do wish they made the other installments but I am happy they wrapped up the parents' storyline I'm still anxious to see the Sinister Six on screen if they ever get around to it just remember Batman & Robin was already dead on arrival, if this one was so bad then why wasn't it boycotted?  they went all out with the merchandise on this one, too, it was truly the most advertised movie of 2014 the bad about this movie to me; it should've been longer to flesh everything else out, Rhino should've been in the movie more as well as Black Cat plus there was so much footage cut from those trailers that I would've loved to see inserted back in that alternate ending with Peter's father coming back was rightfully cut despite some great acting on Garfield's part it stinks too they had Shailene Woodley to shoot scenes as Mary Jane but they ended up omitting all of them I was never a fan of Spider-Man's jokes or one-liners, like come on start taking your job seriously people's lives are in danger! Harry slowly became a villain throughout the course of this movie because he was desperate to ask for Spider-Man's help and he took extreme measures when he was denied therefore feeling betrayed that dark guy in the hat is actually Gustav Feers, he's from a series of Sinister Six novels which in fact Marvel has officially disavowed  Colm Feore as Menken was actually lurking in the background this whole time if you pay attention since Oscorp is more concerned about their stocks and hiding their genetic experiments from the public, they just wanted Harry out of the way by framing him that way they could be in charge yes a lot of people complain they made another Spider-Man 3 with this one but keep in mind that movie still gets a pass and it made a ton of money breaking box office records, if it's still hated by so many fans how come no one acts like it never existed? I still love the trilogy and this one too because they feel colorful, fun, action-packed, filled with enough drama, and have a collection of really good actors Spider-Man: Into the Spiderverse is really fun and entertaining but overall it still feels like a kids movie the MCU Spider-Man movies have yet to still impress me hugely cause it's hard to top that 2002 movie which started something so monumental for the genre Amazing Spider-Man 2 the worst Spider-Man movie? HELL NO! I have yet to see one that actually fails spectacularly still skipping that 2012 movie like the plague

text: Yess im very agree with you. I mean, andrew such an amazing actor that really fits the spidey its self. Spidey is used to be mature guy with sad story behind, and fight hard to protect the city. We all know in the comic, spidey was one of dark heros story. Spiderman homecoming is too childish. Too young to encounter the danger. We know that spidey knowns as "friendly neighbourhood". But its doesnt mean to play spidey with child actor. Im really sad with that spidey homecoming. Andrew really fits enough to be spiderman. And his relationship with gwen, its really serious and complicated but its fits well enough with the story. With all the 3 series of spiderman, this is what i got so far:  1. "Spiderman" tobey maguire is too old for spiderman. Too formal. Not flexible. We dont have enough jokes in this series. As we know that spidey always disarm enemies with jokes. 2. "The Amazing Spiderman" like i said, Andrew garfield was such an amazing actor. His charisma is making us feel like, "this is spiderman should be". He knows to tell a jokes, we can see so much pain and pressure that really struggle spidey in this series. And after all that, we can still enjoy andrew as peter parker as spiderman as your friendly neighbourhood. This is the most spiderman series should be. Its not too adult, and its not too childish. 3. "Spiderman: Homecoming" yeah i know a lot of people still like this movie. Tom holland really make a good job in this series. His jokes still make us comfort with his performance as spidey. But, i dont feel this series maximize the spidey. I dont get the feel. For me, this series its too childish.  And in this the amazing spiderman series, we can enjoy his movement while swinging a web spiders in the town. Its amazing and like andrew does. This is the best and well performance ever.
